<i>Posted by Zantharus on 06-13-2001 08:51 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>Are shamans overpowered? You betcha. Oh, the game *would* be better if ten or eleven of the other classes were as powerful, but shamans in general stand head and shoulders above everyone else. Arkand soloed a level 54 ancient wyvern WITHOUT any level 60 spells, remember? The PoD, BTW, doesn't aggro pets, so any pet class- even an enchanter- could solo it given enough time and boredom.<br />
<br />
(No, a necro couldn't solo Yeldema- not even close. Neither the necro or their pets have the hit points or AC to stand up to an unslowed, summoning dragon, so they'd have to hope that Fear was never resisted, broke early, or wore off over a 20 minute fight- not bloody likely. It might be *technically* possible if you had a necro with a Bladestopper or some such thing in their inventory, but that's about it ^_^)<br />
<br />
Are the items that let you do this 'uber' loot? Not really. If you are level 60 with Torpor and Malo, you *will* have an SoF, a JBB is 15-20k (which you can get in a week of strategic camping), and the fungi tunic is the easiest camp imaginable considering the desirability of the item. Not that you need the JBB or even the fungi (as a lizard/troll) for this fight; although it'd take longer, a fungiless Iksar could do this in a few more minutes (4100 damage=just over 2 extra SoF clicks), and an Iksar WITH a fungi could probably even use DoT's to speed it up.<br />
<br />
Will shamans be nerfed because of this, though? Doubt it. If the old Whineplay was still up, I'd be pretty scared, but now? Three quarters of the submissions never get read, and Abashi has an anti-necro vendetta that means any gripe from a necro won't ever be taken seriously. <br />
<br />
(However, I'd still hope Verant never figures out how to add a recast delay to items, or just how insanely powerful a fungi tunic is...)<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><br>
