<i>Posted by Boinshar on 06-15-2001 07:48 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>The three arguably greatest soloing classes, necros, druids, and shamans, each depends on different things to kill different kind of mobs. There are normally three reasons to solo, bragging rights, exp, and farming items. The three classes are not equal when dealing with these three situations.<br />
<br />
First, lets talk about shamans. The shaman's greatest asset is the ability to use armor, and the spell Turgurs. To be able to solo well a shaman HAS to have decent equipment, if not absolutely needing one of the 3 toys(jbb, fungi, epic) to be able to do certain thing. With good equipment, a shaman is perhaps best at soloing for bragging rights, because all you have to deal with is 1 mob, and that mob is operating at 25% efficiency. With the correct equipment (jbb, fungi, epic) a shaman can almost solo 1 mob at a time non-stop for exp, and with the same equipment a shaman can farm multipul mobs at the same time for items pretty easily.<br />
<br />
Necromancers are 95% dependent on their spells(the pet is a spell), it is the only source of power they have, and to be honest, it's the only source of power they need. The necromancer excels in exp camps and farming, because there is little to no risk involved, and can literally kill things non-stop for a long period of time(my first main was necro, 1-50 took 20 days on a main char with a lvl 34 pet). Necros are slightly less keen when soloing for bragging rights, but as long as fear can land reliably, it's no big deal. Necromancers were the first to solo the Dino in OOT, and was the ONLY class able to do it until shamans gained the necessary equipment to do so. Hence, this is the reason necros go nerfed so much. Other classes depend on a few sources of power, while necros only needed their spells. With spells like harmshield and FD, I don't recall dying even once trying to do something that was deemed "impossible". Is it justified? Each person has his/her own opinion.<br />
<br />
Druids. They are pathetic at bragging-rights type encounters. Anything that summons will kill a druid quickly. They can use decent armor, and with the right equipment they can get to 800ac fairly easily. The ES arms help them with exp soloing quite a bit, since their root line last a lot longer. They are good at farming 1 mob at a time. Because of their lack of a way to regen mana, they cannot farm multipul mobs like shamans and necros. Before kunark, Druids were a distant 2nd after the necros in terms of soloing, but with the introduction of quad kite, they seem to be 1st. However, quad kite is limited to mobs with relatively low HP, and if they get any adds, they have to either gate or zone, there is no other way around it. The greatest problem with a druid compared to the other two is their inability to regen mana quickly, thus they are extremely limited when low on mana.<br />
<br />
Boinshar<br />
Oracle of War</p>
