<i>Posted by kamfool on 06-16-2001 08:12 AM:</i>

<p><b> hi</b></p>

<p>Nixx so powa<br />
<br />
Spells: Torpor: Any shaman that doesn't have Torpor wouldn't be able to do this. Torpor = 1200 hitpoint heal, 300 hitpoints/tick, 4 ticks for 200 mana. This is easily the most mana efficient heal in the game besides complete heal.<br />
<br />
Malo: resistance debuff: cold, fire magic disease blah blah. I don't know if jaundiced bracer does 263 per hit always, but I'm assuming it doesn't, so lower cold resist on target = good. Slow is magic based, lower magic resistance on target = better chances of a slow.<br />
<br />
Canni 4: 148 hitpoints into 78 mana. Canni 3 x2 but without the obscene fizzle rate. This is good. Fizzling wastes a second; wasting time while fighting anything isn't good, obviously.<br />
<br />
Equipment: Spear of fate. The shaman epic, duh.. has a right click effect of a 1200 point dot - splurt based (damage accumulates). Doesn't stack with Splurt, Bond of Death(Vexing Mordinia), or higher level spear dot.<br />
<br />
Jaundiced bone breastplate: I'm assuming Nixx has better, but the effect on the jbbp is a 22 armor 3 damage shield buff. A previous poster mentioned that the bp did 178 damage over the fight. Not much, but I guess that's okay.<br />
<br />
Jaundiced bone bracer: Shaman bracer that has a right click effect of 263 point direct damage spell. = good.<br />
<br />
Fungi tunic: 15 point regrowth added to regen rate.<br />
<br />
Fungi staff: 15 point regrowth added to regen rate, there's a sploit to get normal regrowth and staff regrowth to stack, but I don't.. well, I don't want to tell you. [No, I do not have a staff.]<br />
<br />
Yeld infoz: Yeldema.. level 53 drake/dragon whatever, summons, hits for 180 or so. Slowable, obviously, is not immune to anything.<br />
<br />
Zone crap: West wastes = many dragons, lots of things. To be quite honest with you, the gravid drakes are harder than Yeldema [when I was tanking, anyhow]. It's the roamers that would screw over somebody, not Yeld herself.<br />
<br />
Conclusion.. without a lot of the above mentioned items and spells, the fight is (more or less) impossible. Items and junk alone don't make things doable though - it's the player's skill and understanding of things that make it possible. Nixx has all of these. Hoorah. So powa = nixx<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><br>
__________________<br>
Kamukuk - 58 Troll Shaman, Lanys<br />
Vhaleas - 58 Dark Elf Warrior, Druzzil</font></p>
