<i>Posted by Shamus on 06-16-2001 06:04 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>-------- The necromancer excels in exp camps and farming, because there is little to no risk involved, and can literally kill things non-stop for a long period of time(my first main was necro, 1-50 took 20 days on a main char with a lvl 34 pet). ---------<br />
<br />
        This being said i can very well see a necro get to 50 in 20 days IF he knew exactly where to go to hunt and most likely used an old quest that is not NEARLY as good as it used to be.  If he was a twink then this is a no brainer 20 days is easy.  This is 20 days of play not 20 days on your character i am talking of.  Hell on Luclin it is common knowledge that the first Gravelord was a twink of a 60 shaman named Papazol who did it over the course of 4 weeks.</p>
