<i>Posted by Shamus on 06-17-2001 11:18 AM:</i>

<p><b> ACTUALLY.</b></p>

<p>The quest i was speaking above about was the old(spelling butchered here) Hedi Kiola nut / Trumpy tunic quest in Dwarf city.  It was a quest that gave WAY too much experience and at one point i rememebr them saying people took turns handing stuff to him cause so many people did it at one time it was enough to almost shut down the zone.  VI finally fixed it but i know MANY casting classes and such that did this quest and made lvl 30-40 inside a day or so EASY.  To me that's an exploit but technically it wasn't just bad programming.  Yes, Busseux those lvls are all doable in the times set and sometimes faster.  It's all dependent on how long you will invest at one spot getting exp solo and how efficiently you can do it.  SURE it's way BORING but it's the experience grind we all hate to do but becomes natural post 50. God 59 is the endless lvl, but i finally got my Fungus Tunic!!<br />
             Shamus</p>
