<i>Posted by Blore on 06-24-2001 11:57 AM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>one thing that i think hasn't been mentioned when comparing the solo abilities of shamans and necros is that while a shaman solo impressively, shamans cannot do it for much gain. this is because of the efficiency involved.. a shaman has to do his damage SLOWLY, and if the mob is at all challenging, will spend alot of mana during the fight, either healing or with dots. so the mobs die slower AND the shaman needs to rest up before pulling again. where as a necro can virtually continue killing endlessly with lich + and lifetaps.<br />
<br />
so while a necro can 'farm' mobs for xp and loot, a shaman cant anywhere near as quickly.  the best use of shamans soloing tough mobs like this is really only so they can say they did. and i admit its fun to solo tough things and brag, but its not overpowering, because we dont gain much. it is still far more efficient, kill per hour wise, to duo with a melee.<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF"><br>
__________________<br>
Bloregarr the Mystic<br />
Tunare</font></p>
