<i>Posted by Valka on 06-25-2001 06:53 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>Clearly this is not something your 'average' shaman can do, and it isn't easy even then<br />
since more than 1 resist on turgors probably means you're dead, and you are most definitely dead if you get any adds throughout the course of the (long) fight.<br />
<br />
To make this possible you need to be 60, with more or less a full spellbook and<br />
plenty of rather difficult to aquire gear.<br />
<br />
(ie. epic+fungi+jbb gear wise, along with enough ac gear to stay alive for the duration)<br />
<br />
You'd also need at minimum malo, torpor, and cann4. These are not necessarily easy to aquire,<br />
they drop quite rarely in fact. (cann4 is not a hard drop, but malo is, as is torpor). <br />
<br />
So,Yes this is impressive, IMO No this is no reason to break out nerf bats-o-doom. <br />
Enchanters are just as capable of killing 'bragging rights' mobs like this one providing there are tough charmable mobs in the area (there are). They require no 'uber' gear to do it, just charm, haste and gate. For Fearable mobs (this one may not be) Necromancers can likewise go to town with much lower risk. <br />
<br />
-Valka</p>
